Remember the days when wizard nukes were big and impressive, and your whole career was geared towards a bigger, more impressive nuke, and making a trouble mob die -now-?<br>
<br>
They have said they wouldn't improve Mana regeneration.<br>
They have said they wouldn't improve damage over time.<br>
They have said they wouldn't improve damage/mana ratios.<br>
<br>
Well, a lot of what we do isn't strictly efficiency oriented if you -really- look at it.  On the surface we are a really simple class.  the deeper you look, the more complex we get.  What if... instead of our pressing them to change things they have said they wouldn't, we try to get them to make different changes?  <br>
<br>
Our single strike single target nukes get bigger and bigger until 49, and then shrink back down until 60, when they finally eclipse good old Ice Comet.  Why don't they give us big frigging nukes with slightly-better-than-IC mana costs and extended recast times?<br>
<br>
You can't solo with a nuke you can only cast once in a fight.  Start with Frost Comet (an upgrade to IC), then add Inferno, then Lightning.  <br>
<br>
At about 55, start adding in double resistance check nukes.  Spells that cast both fire and ice damage, fire and magic, ice and magic.  This way a properly debuffed mob takes a severe beating from wizzies.<br>
<br>
Another possible idea would be utility spells that push the mob back constantly.. a magical wind line.  It could function like a rain spell, in that the attack was dealt in waves.  It wouldn't help worth jack if we were trying to solo, because the monster could just run towards us and melee us to bits, but it would stop mobs from casting.<br>
<br>
How about adding a spell that made it so wizards could stop mobs specifically from running off at the end of a battle?  Similar to snaring the mob as we do now, but rather than taking effect over the rest of the battle, it could just kick in (or be cast) when the mob tries to wimpy at 20%?  Sort of like a mime trapped in a box.<br>
<br>
Last but not least, since high levelled wizards are so specifically oriented towards dealing damage, and those little greenie meanies always seem to pop up at the wrong time and soak up our much needed mana reserves, what about a self only Fear shield spell?  Easily resisted by mobs that were within a certain level range, it would only work on lower levelled mobs, but it would stop those annoying damn skeletons and drachnids from harassing us.  Instead, they would run like hell in the other direction.  It could fear them, drop their aggro, and buff the mob's movement rate, so that they ran too quickly for someone to take advantage of it by snaring them first.<br>
<br>
Shylote Painbringer<br>
Wizard of 57 Tiers of Punishment<br>
&quot;Rogues remind me of the Flaming Sword of Xuzl.. small, annoying, and always missing at the end of the fight.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 343<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/14/01 8:38 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Predictable...</span><hr size=1> A very creative set of ideas.  Mob stopping and all.  I truly believe the response would be along the lines of...<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Wizards already have that ability in snare.  We see no need to create another.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
That is the sort of idea I would like to see.  Its creative, its individualistic, its not unbalancing...  assuming we were balanced to being with.  After talking with him face to face a couple times, his responses truly take on the &quot;broken record&quot; quality.  Which is a shame.<br>
<br>
